        21st February 2025

        I decided to create a profile here after I watched a video of Richard Osman that's gone viral about how there's been a complete purging of bands from the brunt of the Singles Chart in the UK. I had to see it for myself.

        Before it updates, look through this chart. I counted around 90ish of the 100 songs on this chart are entries from solo singers/singer songwriters/duos/collabs of solo artists/trios

        There IS truly a lack of bands, and what's more, the few bands that appear on this chart are bands that have been around for decades, like Fleetwood Mac.

        The only bands on here that formed in the past 10 years are Fontaines DC and Marias!

        What happened?! In that video I mentioned, Osman mentions how in the first half of the 1980s, bands (that being, a group of people, all playing their own instruments, often with a frontman, who write their own songs and so forth) spent a total of 146 weeks at No.1, Dexys, UB40, KC and Sunshine, Duran Duran, Culture Club, Pretenders, Spandau, Adam and the Ants, Human League,

        Everyone do yourselves a favour, get bands back in the charts, go to iTunes and actually buy Fontaines DC's new single, It's Amazing To Be Young.

        mathsnumbers

        15th February 2025

        Vote score

        Ranked the lot of em this time!


        S TIER


        Good Luck, Babe! - Chappell Roan (22) -This song just has such a good theme and character. It's melodically amazing, and the lyrics convey the theme brilliantly. I wanted this to hit number one so badly last year, and maybe she's got a second chance withPink Pony Club (4).I really hope her next album (which will have this on it no doubt) gains more chart success.

        Beautiful Things - Benson Boone (6) -Such a strong melody with such meaningful lyrics that really make me feel good. Although he is almost the polar opposite of Chappell Roan, I think that the pair of them have outstanding melodic talent.

        A TIER

        That's So True - Gracie Abrams (14) -I'm not normally a huge fan of guitar-pop but this one is really impressive melodically. Her singing is right in the zone. She's released some other music that would hit S Tier (namelyClose To YouandFeels Like) that should have gained more love in the chart. Still a fantastic hit though.

        Sailor Song - G.G. Perez (29) -On the subject of guitar-pop, here's one where the accompaniment is made up of almost all guitar. For me, the theme and lyrics are what puts this so high - it's a pretty emotional piece of music. Once again, a really talented artist.

        Pink Pony Club - Chappell Roan (4) -Amazing, but not quite at the level ofGood Luck, Babe! (22).

        Apt. - ROSE and Bruno Mars (8) -A super-catchy, lively hit. Probably the best feel-good song on here for most people. I expect that next week it's gonna rise up to the top again. It would be cool if it hit number one - finally!

        Birds of a Feather - Billie Eilish (26) -For me, there isn't enough melody here. Still a good one though!

        Taste - Sabrina Carpenter (40) -The most tolerable of Sabrina's work. The video is weird but the song itself isn't that bad.

        Espresso - Sabrina Carpenter (33) -This should really be in C Tier but I think that it's become such a staple of the charts that it gains a few points. I used to quite like it but now I think it's too repetitive.

        CRG - Central Cee and Dave (24)-One of the first half-decent raps I've heard sinceBACKBONEby Chase + Status. Obviously because it's rap it can't be that high, but I think that Central Cee is one of the more musical rappers.

        C TIER

        [All songs in the Top 40 I didn't mention.]


        D TIER

        GBP - Central Cee feet. 21 Savage (30) -Not at all my style of music. Central Cee is one of the least worst rappers though, as I mentioned above. Still too rhythmic for me.

        Dirty Cash, Money Talks - Pawsa feet. Adventures of Steevie V (27) -I think it's too repetitive and the theme isn't great. So, one of the less good ones this week.


        E TIER

        Like Him - Tyler, the Creator and Lola Young and Lola Young (38) -Not a cool theme, and a horrible melodic bit at the end.

        Red Wine Supernova - Chappell Roan (32) -The only song by Chappell Roan that I dislike. It's too "campy", in my opinion.


        F TIER

        Guess - Charli XCX feet. Billie Eilish (21) -Not the way to get a debut number one single. A rushed rap with bad themes. Some may say it's a laugh but for me it's nothing more than someone making a Tick Tock video or something, that you can do in a couple of free minutes.

        Bad Chem - Sabrina Carpenter (25) -The worst song that has ever hit the charts. Rushed, terrible melody and the words...
